ce:section.ce:para:
In a conical flask, 100 mg of GQDs and 300 mg of Mg-PMA powders were introduced and subsequently dissolved in 70 mL of distilled water. The resultant solution underwent sonication for a duration of 2 h, followed by filtration, and was thereafter subjected to a dialysis process for 6 h utilizing distilled water. The dialyzed solution was subsequently transferred into a 100-mL volumetric flask, where the volume was calibrated with distilled water, and the preparation was preserved at a temperature of 4 °C. The functionalized GQDs (F-GQDs) exhibited a distinct emission peak (F

                           0
                        ) at 445 nm after excitation at 352 nm.
